{
  "texts": [
    "In the next subsections, the robotic concepts used in this thesis are explained.",
    "Degree of Freedom (DOF)An articulated robotic arm is made up of interconnected links and rotary joints leading to an end-effector.",
    "The total number of these joints indicates the robotic arm's DOF, with each joint typically powered by servomotors that supply the needed torque for link rotation.",
    "Microcontrollers manage the servomotors' angular movements by delivering the necessary electrical signals for control [34].",
    "In fact, in robotics, the term degree of freedom refers to the number of independent movements or axes of motion that a robot or robotic mechanism can control."
  ]
}